definition.value: An ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of N-methylphenylethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of creatine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the guanidino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 5-oxo-D-proline; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of 6-phospho-5-dehydro-2-deoxy-D-gluconic acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of 2,5-diaminohexanoic acid resulting from protonation of both amino groups and deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of L-saccharopine arising from deprotonation of all three carboxy groups and protonation of the primary and secondary amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine arising from transfer of a proton from the phospho to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanine arising from deprotonation of diphosphate and alanine carboxy groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 3-cyano-L-alanine; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of 6-O-phosphono-D-glucono-1,5-lactone arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of 3-amino-3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)propanoic acid arising from migration of a proton fron the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of lipid X arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 3-dehydro-L-threonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-kynurenine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of 5-hydroxymethyldeoxycytidylic acid arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of vitexin arising from deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of GDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-mannose arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of deacetoxyvindoline arising from protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of beta-alanine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the dianion of ADP-D-ribose(2-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Tetraanion of UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamic acid arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate and glutamate carboxy groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of imidazol-4-ylacetic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of a 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An ammonium ion that is the trication of hygromycin B arising from protonation of the three amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-alanine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The leukotriene anion that is the dianion of leukotriene C4 arising from deprotonation of the three carboxy groups and protonation of the glutamyl alpha-amino group.
Zwitterionic form of O-(3-O-D-galactosyl-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl)-L-serine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A pyridinium ion having methyl and 2-hydroxyethyl groups at positions 2 and 3 respectively as well as a 4-hydroxy-2-methylpyrimid-5-ylmethyl attached to the nitrogen.
Trianion of 2-(carboxymethyl)-5-oxo-2,5-dihydro-3-furoic acid arising from deprotonation of the two carboxy groups as well as removal of the acidic proton at C2; major species at pH 7.3.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of bilirubin; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 2-hydroxy-3-oxopropanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dicarboxylate anion of 2-(carboxymethyl)-5-oxo-2,5-dihydro-2-furoic acid.
Conjugate base of L-histidinol phosphate having an anionic phosphate and a catoinic amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that is D-phenylalanine in which a proton has been transferred from the carboxy group to the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero 3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as (S)-12-hydroxyoleoyl.
Dianion of GDP-L-fucose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of S-inosyl-L-homocysteine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of riboflavin resulting from the removal of a proton from the nitrogen at position 3 (between the two carbonyl groups). Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Dicarboxylate anion of 2-hydroxyadipic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of allysine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-galactonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dicarboxylate anion of biliverdin; major species at pH 7.3.
Tricarboxylate anion of (carboxymethoxy)succinic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of (S)-N-methylcoclaurine; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of tetrachlorohydroquinone arising from deprotonation of both phenol groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of all-trans-undecaprenyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of nororientaline; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of a 6-(alpha-D-glucosaminyl)-1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH.
Trianion of 3-phosphoglyceric acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups; major species at pH 7.3.
